======================================================================
PART 1: A_6 AUSLANDER-REITEN QUIVER
======================================================================

  A_6 has 21 indecomposable representations:
  (= positive roots = Gabriel number = 21)
    dim 1: M(1,1), M(2,2), M(3,3), M(4,4), M(5,5), M(6,6)  (6 modules)
    dim 2: M(1,2), M(2,3), M(3,4), M(4,5), M(5,6)  (5 modules)
    dim 3: M(1,3), M(2,4), M(3,5), M(4,6)  (4 modules)
    dim 4: M(1,4), M(2,5), M(3,6)  (3 modules)
    dim 5: M(1,5), M(2,6)  (2 modules)
    dim 6: M(1,6)  (1 modules)

  AR quiver arrows (irreducible morphisms):
    30 arrows total

  KEY: 21 = H_forb_2 = # indecomposable A_6-representations
  A_6 has rank 6, Coxeter number h = 7 = H_forb_1
  Self-referential: H_forb_1 = h(A_6), H_forb_2 = |Phi+(A_6)|

  Module count by total dimension:
    dim 1: 6 modules (6 = 7-d)
    dim 2: 5 modules (5 = 7-d)
    dim 3: 4 modules (4 = 7-d)
    dim 4: 3 modules (3 = 7-d)
    dim 5: 2 modules (2 = 7-d)
    dim 6: 1 modules (1 = 7-d)
    Sum: 6+5+4+3+2+1 = 21 = T_6 (6th triangular number)

  21 = T_6 = C(7,2) = triangular number
  This IS the reason: |Phi+(A_n)| = T_n = C(n+1,2) = n(n+1)/2

