PART 2: TITS QUADRATIC FORM
======================================================================

  A_6: 21 positive roots
  All q(alpha) = 1? True
  E_6: 36 positive roots, all q = 1? True
  E_7: 63 positive roots, all q = 1? True
  E_8: 120 positive roots, all q = 1? True

  Tits form for A_6: q(d) = sum d_i^2 - sum d_i*d_{i+1}
  This is POSITIVE DEFINITE on Z^6 (Dynkin property)
  q(d) = 1 <=> d is a positive root (Gabriel's theorem)

