======================================================================
PART 6: RATE-DISTORTION PERSPECTIVE
======================================================================

  In rate-distortion theory, we ask:
    Given a source (tournaments) and a fidelity criterion,
    what is the minimum rate needed to represent tournaments
    within distortion D?

  The H map is a FIXED encoder with:
    Rate = H(output) / C(n,2)  (fraction of bits retained)

  Distortion metric on tournaments:
    d(T, T') = (Hamming distance on arc encodings) / C(n,2)
    This is the fraction of arcs that differ.

  Maximum distortion within an H-fiber:
    Two tournaments with same H can differ in many arcs.
    
  n=5 fiber analysis:
    H=  1:  120 tournaments, max Hamming dist = 10/10 = 1.000
    H=  3:  120 tournaments, max Hamming dist = 10/10 = 1.000
    H=  5:  240 tournaments, max Hamming dist = 10/10 = 1.000
    H=  9:  240 tournaments, max Hamming dist = 10/10 = 1.000
    H= 11:  120 tournaments, max Hamming dist = 10/10 = 1.000
    H= 13:  120 tournaments, max Hamming dist = 10/10 = 1.000
    H= 15:   64 tournaments, max Hamming dist = 10/10 = 1.000

======================================================================
PART 7: ARC FLIP GRAPH STRUCTURE
======================================================================

  The arc flip graph on n-vertex tournaments:
  - Vertices: 2^C(n,2) tournaments
  - Edges: flip one arc
  - This IS the C(n,2)-dimensional hypercube!
  - H(T) assigns an odd integer to each hypercube vertex
  - H is a labeling of the hypercube with forbidden labels {7, 21, ...}

  n=5 arc flip H-changes:
    Delta H distribution (signed):
      delta =  -12:    20 flips
      delta =   -8:   180 flips
      delta =   -6:   300 flips
      delta =   -4:   600 flips
      delta =   -2:   900 flips
      delta =   +0:  1120 flips
      delta =   +2:   900 flips
      delta =   +4:   600 flips
      delta =   +6:   300 flips
      delta =   +8:   180 flips
      delta =  +12:    20 flips

    Symmetry check: delta(d) = delta(-d)?
    Symmetric? True
    Possible |delta|: [0, 2, 4, 6, 8, 12]
    All even? True

